cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it presents a black-box attack against API call based machine learning malware classifiers. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the transferability principle between different types of classifiers. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it proposes a software framework for converting malware binaries. The paper also involves techniques from cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with machine learning and the behavior of malware in networks.
